7-05-16T16:37:35Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I use the following code and get the following error:\n\n```\nuse std::ops::DerefMut;\n\nstruct Foo<T>\nwhere T: DerefMut\n{\n  member: *mut <T as DerefMut>::Target,\n}\n\ntrait Bar<T>\nwhere T: DerefMut\n{\n  fn foo<'a>(&'a self) -> &'a Foo<T>;\n  fn member<'a>(&'a self) -> &'a *mut <T as DerefMut>::Target {\n    &self.foo().member\n  }\n}\n\n<anon>:15:10: 15:20 error: the parameter type `T` may not live long enough [E0309]\n<anon>:15 &self.foo().member\n           ^~~~~~~~~~\n<anon>:15:10: 15:20 help: consider adding an explicit lifetime bound `T: 'a`...\n<anon>:15 &self.foo().member\n           ^~~~~~~~~~\n<anon>:15:10: 15:20 note: ...so that the reference type `&Foo<T>` does not outlive the data it points at\n<anon>:15 &self.foo().member\n           ^~~~~~~~~~\nerror: aborting due to previous error \n```\n\nI'm not sure why this is an error or why I should have to bound the type T - I never directly use a type T here. I asked on IRC and others were similarly stumped. Indeed if I bound T: 'static then it compiles but it seems unnecessary.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_u